1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:04,400
THIS FICTIONAL SERIES IS INTENDED
FOR ENTERTAINMENT PURPOSES ONLY

2
00:02:44,479 --> 00:02:47,080
You know, don't you, that Gla

3
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:48,759
isn't my own son?

4
00:02:50,319 --> 00:02:53,080
His garage customizes tax-dodging cars,
so it's being raided.

5
00:02:53,159 --> 00:02:54,000
If he's arrested,

6
00:02:54,080 --> 00:02:55,840
Saikhim has nowhere to go.

7
00:02:55,919 --> 00:02:57,000
Marry me, Khim.

8
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:59,039
I won't make you regret

9
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:01,919
giving up your future
to be with someone like me.

10
00:03:02,439 --> 00:03:03,960
Today is the first day

11
00:03:04,039 --> 00:03:07,080
of the rest of your lives
as lawfully wedded husband and wife.

12
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:08,520
Kissing practice.

13
00:03:08,599 --> 00:03:10,800
You'll feel less awkward,
or you'll get punished.

14
00:03:10,879 --> 00:03:11,879
You closed it?

15
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,120
Where's the money?

16
00:03:13,199 --> 00:03:14,879
I gave it to Khem for his own--

17
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:18,360
I gave him all the money
'cause I got a power plant surveying gig.

18
00:03:18,439 --> 00:03:21,039
I'll go to the forests of Laos
with the engineers.

19
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:24,439
I want to make all that money back
before our baby is born.

20
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:25,639
I have learned

21
00:03:26,479 --> 00:03:28,039
that love is most fragile

22
00:03:28,120 --> 00:03:29,599
when you have fears and doubts.

23
00:03:30,159 --> 00:03:31,560
Love is strongest

24
00:03:32,159 --> 00:03:33,960
when you have trust and certainty.

25
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:03,120
Well? What are you staring at?

26
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,479
What are you doing here?

27
00:04:08,159 --> 00:04:09,360
I came to surprise you.

28
00:04:11,319 --> 00:04:12,240
Surprise?

29
00:04:13,199 --> 00:04:15,479
What if I'd died of shock?

30
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,439
Then you'd be a scary pregnant ghost.

31
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,000
I'm not laughing.

32
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,120
Are you really mad?

33
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:36,600
I've missed you so much
for almost a month.

34
00:04:37,879 --> 00:04:39,439
Please don't look so grumpy.

35
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:24,399
Let me see you.

36
00:05:25,199 --> 00:05:26,199
Hey, put it down.

37
00:05:35,079 --> 00:05:36,480
Why didn't you put on weight?

38
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,000
Don't you eat?

39
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:41,319
Hey, kid, you're not too hungry, are you?

40
00:05:42,639 --> 00:05:43,879
Mommy's not eating.

41
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,680
Why is Mommy like this?

42
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:52,279
It's okay, kid. Daddy's home.

43
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:55,560
Don't worry, you won't starve.
I've brought you something.

44
00:05:57,519 --> 00:05:58,680
You've brought something?

45
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:09,839
I've replaced your broken one.

46
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:11,360
I have money now.

47
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,680
I'll pay it off for you.

48
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:15,560
Thank you.

49
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,959
I'll make good use of it.

50
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:31,480
I have to go back next week
to survey the potential tunnel site.

51
00:06:32,079 --> 00:06:33,399
It'll be even harder work.

52
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:36,480
You're leaving again?

53
00:06:38,199 --> 00:06:39,439
I'm here just one week.

54
00:06:39,519 --> 00:06:41,439
I'll make you both nice and fat.

55
00:06:42,879 --> 00:06:43,720
What?

56
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:45,759
What happened?

57
00:06:47,839 --> 00:06:49,319
Why are your hands so filthy?

58
00:06:49,839 --> 00:06:50,959
They're covered in dirt.

59
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:53,079
Well, I've been working.

60
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:55,759
I'm back now.

61
00:06:57,439 --> 00:06:59,079
You can be a lady of leisure again.

62
00:07:00,519 --> 00:07:01,360
Okay?

63
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:27,000
Work your magic, Mama Ooi.

64
00:07:27,079 --> 00:07:28,959
-Sure.
-Make her hands soft again.

65
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,680
Make them smoother than my face.

66
00:07:31,959 --> 00:07:35,639
You're newlyweds, right?
That's why you're so lovey-dovey.

67
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:39,120
Sorry, my honeymoon period will go on
for decades to come.

68
00:07:39,879 --> 00:07:41,360
Decades?

69
00:07:41,439 --> 00:07:43,680
Make it to the end of this year first.

70
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:46,879
Give me your hand.

71
00:07:57,959 --> 00:07:59,120
What is it?

72
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,839
Is he seeing someone else?

73
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:18,000
Excuse me.

74
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,000
Yes, Auntie Oon?

75
00:08:26,079 --> 00:08:28,759
Miss Khim, I have some news.

76
00:08:28,839 --> 00:08:31,959
I've heard that Mr. Seen isn't very well.

77
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,159
Is Dad all right?

78
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:39,000
Your father had a fall.
It might be due to his blood pressure.

79
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:42,120
The doctor said he's at risk for a stroke.

80
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,840
How's Dad doing now?

81
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:47,120
He's just left the hospital.

82
00:08:47,639 --> 00:08:51,080
I've heard he's going to stay
at a friend's plantation near yours.

83
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,320
Really?

84
00:08:55,039 --> 00:08:57,919
Miss Khim, won't you go and visit him?

85
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:05,480
Does he really want to see me, Auntie Oon?

86
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:19,480
You knew the risks,
so why did you take this job?

87
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:24,679
How else could I make a living, bro?
I tried to open my garage and got scammed.

88
00:09:24,759 --> 00:09:26,360
Will this be worth the risks?

89
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,799
Well, I accepted this job

90
00:09:27,879 --> 00:09:29,799
because it's close to your home.

91
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:32,279
We'll just drive across the border.

92
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:35,919
Once we've delivered the stuff,
we'll get all the money, bro.

93
00:09:39,879 --> 00:09:40,720
I can't do it.

94
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,639
I promised Khim I wouldn't do crime again.

95
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:45,080
Okay, bro.

96
00:09:46,559 --> 00:09:47,559
I'll do it alone.

97
00:09:49,039 --> 00:09:53,360
Khem, if you really have money problems,
I can find ways to borrow money for you.

98
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:55,159
Don't put yourself at risk, okay?

99
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:56,840
Don't worry, bro.

100
00:09:58,840 --> 00:10:00,600
I don't want to trouble you again.

101
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:05,279
Hey, Khem…

102
00:10:38,879 --> 00:10:40,679
I charged the battery for you.

103
00:10:40,759 --> 00:10:42,759
You have to go to the forests prepared

104
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,159
so we can stay in touch.

105
00:10:47,039 --> 00:10:49,080
I love having someone to worry about me.

106
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:53,799
Don't complain if I call you too often.

107
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:07,600
If only I could bring you
as a spare battery.

108
00:11:08,919 --> 00:11:11,879
When I'm tired,
I think of you, and I feel stronger.

109
00:11:12,399 --> 00:11:17,639
I don't know where that energy comes from.
I want you near me so you can recharge me.

110
00:11:20,519 --> 00:11:21,360
In that case,

111
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:24,080
I'll fully recharge you right now.

112
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:30,639
What? I haven't been home long.
I need more time to recharge.

113
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:33,240
I'm still tired. What should we do?

114
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,519
Can I charge my spare battery?

115
00:12:23,919 --> 00:12:26,720
You don't have to see me off.
Save yourself the long trip.

116
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,279
This is far enough.

117
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:33,440
Look after yourself.

118
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,279
Don't work too hard, Dad.

119
00:13:01,879 --> 00:13:03,039
Hang on.

120
00:13:11,159 --> 00:13:12,120
It's so cute, Khim.

121
00:13:13,799 --> 00:13:15,200
Hurry back, okay?

122
00:13:16,399 --> 00:13:17,639
You take care, okay?

123
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,080
You take care too.

124
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:30,919
Bye.

125
00:13:50,240 --> 00:13:52,000
You want to see Daddy off, do you?

126
00:13:53,679 --> 00:13:55,759
Gla!

127
00:14:18,159 --> 00:14:20,159
Gla, the baby's moving.

128
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:32,200
Why are so many cops around today?

129
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,399
Is there trouble again?

130
00:14:37,519 --> 00:14:40,120
Maybe there's
another counterfeit goods raid.

131
00:14:45,519 --> 00:14:46,600
Khem.

132
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:17,240
-Let's go that way.
-What? Aren't we going to the border?

133
00:15:17,759 --> 00:15:19,679
I need to do something. Turn that way.

134
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:21,039
Okay.

135
00:15:31,559 --> 00:15:33,159
Hey, man, stop right here.

136
00:15:36,159 --> 00:15:37,000
You can go now.

137
00:15:44,799 --> 00:15:46,360
Khem! Are you around here?

138
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:49,039
Hey, Khem!

139
00:15:50,879 --> 00:15:51,960
-Khem!
-Bro!

140
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:54,919
-What are you doing here?
-What are you waiting for?

141
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,639
There are checkpoints everywhere.

142
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:57,600
Don't take the car!

143
00:15:58,879 --> 00:16:00,879
This gun, it was in the car.

144
00:16:01,759 --> 00:16:03,360
Stop! Freeze!

145
00:16:07,279 --> 00:16:08,159
Run, Khem!

146
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:09,399
Bro…

147
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:12,159
Don't move! Put the weapon down!

148
00:16:20,759 --> 00:16:21,840
What should we do?

149
00:16:21,919 --> 00:16:22,919
Give me the gun.

150
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:23,919
Don't move!

151
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:36,840
Freeze!

152
00:16:38,399 --> 00:16:40,080
Put the weapon down slowly.

153
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,159
Hey!

154
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:49,039
-Khem, get in the car!
-Okay!

155
00:17:00,039 --> 00:17:01,799
-Hey!
-Hey, bro!

156
00:17:01,879 --> 00:17:02,840
Hey!

157
00:17:04,799 --> 00:17:05,720
Hey!

158
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:25,400
Mr. Seen is staying in the area.

159
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:28,160
I heard that you were here, Miss Khim,

160
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:29,880
so I've come to bring you to him.

161
00:17:32,079 --> 00:17:34,440
Does he really want me to see him?

162
00:17:36,119 --> 00:17:37,200
I'm worried

163
00:17:38,079 --> 00:17:39,839
that if he sees me,

164
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:42,319
he won't be able to cope.

165
00:17:55,279 --> 00:17:57,079
How will we get away from them?

166
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:58,920
You wanna die in jail an old man?

167
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:01,960
Hey, what now, bro?

168
00:19:02,039 --> 00:19:03,519
We have to leave the car.

169
00:19:13,759 --> 00:19:14,839
Khem.

170
00:19:25,599 --> 00:19:28,079
-Hey, here's our way out of this!
-Hey!

171
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:31,319
Gla! The cops!

172
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:32,920
-Stop!
-Stop! This is the police!

173
00:19:33,519 --> 00:19:34,680
-Hey!
-Khem! Come on!

174
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:38,279
I'm coming, bro.

175
00:19:38,359 --> 00:19:39,440
Stop!

176
00:19:48,559 --> 00:19:49,920
Gla, hurry!

177
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:03,839
Come in. We need backup right now.
The suspects are fleeing by boat.

178
00:20:33,799 --> 00:20:34,920
Move! Hurry!

179
00:20:35,519 --> 00:20:36,559
Lock onto the target!

180
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:41,720
Hey! The cops!

181
00:20:42,119 --> 00:20:43,319
Gla! The cops!

182
00:20:48,359 --> 00:20:49,200
Turn, bro!

183
00:21:08,319 --> 00:21:09,200
My family called.

184
00:21:19,279 --> 00:21:20,799
Please stop here.

185
00:21:28,839 --> 00:21:30,559
Uncle?

186
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:34,920
Is something wrong?

187
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:37,920
It's Gla. He didn't go to the border.

188
00:21:39,319 --> 00:21:40,640
He's causing trouble again.

189
00:21:59,119 --> 00:22:01,039
Please keep out. It's dangerous.

190
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:04,079
Please keep out. It's dangerous.

191
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:07,920
-Gla!
-I'm coming too.

192
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:09,640
-Gla!
-Don't enter.

193
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:11,799
Officers! My son is there!

194
00:22:12,319 --> 00:22:14,319
-Sir, it's dangerous.
-Can I go in there?

195
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:15,799
No, ma'am. It's dangerous.

196
00:22:17,759 --> 00:22:20,839
We've surrounded the suspects.
They won't get away.

197
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:21,960
We're doomed!

198
00:22:25,039 --> 00:22:25,880
Surrender now!

199
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:32,480
-Be careful, Miss Khim.
-Keep out.

200
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:35,200
-Please let me in.
-No, it's too dangerous.

201
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:45,880
Fire!

202
00:22:53,279 --> 00:22:54,160
Khem!

203
00:22:54,240 --> 00:22:55,359
A suspect has been shot.

204
00:22:56,279 --> 00:22:57,119
Gla.

205
00:23:00,839 --> 00:23:02,240
Put your hands up!

206
00:23:02,319 --> 00:23:03,640
You're not getting away!

207
00:23:20,599 --> 00:23:21,640
Get on the boat!

208
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:22,559
Move! Hurry!

209
00:23:26,559 --> 00:23:27,640
Uncle?

210
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:37,519
If they refuse to be taken alive,
we'll take them dead.

211
00:24:01,079 --> 00:24:01,920
Khem!

212
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:05,799
Khem! Wake up!

213
00:24:09,559 --> 00:24:10,440
Stop!

214
00:24:13,039 --> 00:24:14,519
Don't you dare give up!

215
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:19,079
Put your hands up and surrender!

216
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:20,000
Khem!

217
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:22,279
Don't leave me like this!

218
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:25,720
Attention.

219
00:24:27,359 --> 00:24:28,680
Our informant is dying.

220
00:24:29,599 --> 00:24:30,440
Informant?

221
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:38,079
We just want Saikhim back,

222
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:41,039
and we want Gaogla
to admit that he abducted her.

223
00:24:42,519 --> 00:24:45,720
Then we'll find ways to help you
with your vehicle fraud case.

224
00:24:49,759 --> 00:24:53,400
Get Gaogla to surrender
and let the man have his daughter back

225
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:56,240
if you don't want a life sentence.

226
00:25:00,519 --> 00:25:01,559
I'm sorry.

227
00:25:03,519 --> 00:25:06,000
Listen! We've seized all the evidence!

228
00:25:06,759 --> 00:25:09,440
The case against you is ironclad.
Give yourself up now!

229
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:11,119
How could you?

230
00:25:12,119 --> 00:25:15,759
-Why did you do it?
-I didn't think it would end like this.

231
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:19,680
I'm sorry, bro.

232
00:25:19,759 --> 00:25:21,680
Do not resist arrest or try to flee!

233
00:25:22,359 --> 00:25:23,559
Why did you do it?

234
00:25:29,839 --> 00:25:32,559
If I can't be good,
I'll just give up and be bad!

235
00:25:58,240 --> 00:25:59,079
Let's go.

236
00:26:00,440 --> 00:26:02,240
Out of our way, please.

237
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,599
Out of our way, please.

238
00:27:21,160 --> 00:27:22,000
Dad?

239
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:26,279
How are you?

240
00:27:29,759 --> 00:27:30,599
What about Gla?

241
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:33,519
All our actions have consequences.

242
00:27:36,160 --> 00:27:38,559
So, is Gla safe?

243
00:27:39,559 --> 00:27:40,839
-I have to see him!
-Khim.

244
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:42,359
You have to stay here.

245
00:27:43,640 --> 00:27:44,480
Listen.

246
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:47,720
Even if he survives,
he won't stay out of jail.

247
00:27:47,799 --> 00:27:48,640
You as well.

248
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:51,960
He could drag you down with him
if you don't leave him.

249
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:54,759
Gla did nothing wrong, Dad.

250
00:27:54,839 --> 00:27:57,480
He promised me
that he'd change for the better.

251
00:27:57,559 --> 00:27:59,599
People who are used to living recklessly

252
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:01,599
promise to change their ways,

253
00:28:02,119 --> 00:28:04,680
but do you know
what they're doing behind your back?

254
00:28:09,319 --> 00:28:10,160
Here.

255
00:28:10,839 --> 00:28:11,680
Take a look.

256
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:15,680
He threatened

257
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:17,880
to make this public.

258
00:28:19,039 --> 00:28:21,720
And he said that your unborn baby

259
00:28:21,799 --> 00:28:23,359
will not be his responsibility.

260
00:28:24,880 --> 00:28:26,839
That's why he distanced himself from you.

261
00:28:28,079 --> 00:28:28,920
That's not true.

262
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:32,359
-It's not true. I need to see him, Dad!
-Khim.

263
00:28:33,559 --> 00:28:35,039
Khim, listen to me.

264
00:28:35,920 --> 00:28:37,960
You don't even know him that well.

265
00:28:38,559 --> 00:28:41,400
You don't love him. You never did.
It's just an infatuation.

266
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:44,759
That's not true.

267
00:28:44,839 --> 00:28:45,759
-Khim.
-No!

268
00:28:46,319 --> 00:28:48,400
-Gla!
-You don't love him. You're infatuated.

269
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:50,039
It's only infatuation. Trust me.

270
