Since Mom's death,

733
01:07:43,559 --> 01:07:45,480
you've suffered so much because of me.

734
01:07:46,159 --> 01:07:47,039
From now on,

735
01:07:47,920 --> 01:07:50,239
please let me do my duty as your son.

736
01:07:52,800 --> 01:07:56,000
I want you to be comfortable,
to have everything you need,

737
01:07:56,719 --> 01:07:58,920
and to hold your head up high.

738
01:07:59,960 --> 01:08:01,119
Keep your plantation.

739
01:08:01,880 --> 01:08:03,960
Don't waste it on this wayward son.

740
01:08:04,719 --> 01:08:05,559
This money

741
01:08:06,840 --> 01:08:08,280
is my way of paying my debt.

742
01:08:09,239 --> 01:08:10,440
Use it to save Gloy.

743
01:08:12,239 --> 01:08:13,079
Gloy!

744
01:08:14,960 --> 01:08:15,800
Gloy, honey!

745
01:08:27,039 --> 01:08:30,239
If she survives,
pay for her to go to good schools

746
01:08:31,079 --> 01:08:32,319
so she'll get a degree.

747
01:08:33,520 --> 01:08:35,159
You could buy a big new car.

748
01:08:45,000 --> 01:08:45,840
All my life,

749
01:08:46,680 --> 01:08:48,640
I've never made you proud.

750
01:08:49,159 --> 01:08:50,600
This might be my last chance

751
01:08:51,399 --> 01:08:52,680
to do something for you.

752
01:08:57,920 --> 01:08:59,560
Who knows what will happen next?

753
01:09:01,000 --> 01:09:02,319
If reincarnation is real,

754
01:09:03,680 --> 01:09:05,439
I hope I get to be your son again.

755
01:09:06,680 --> 01:09:10,199
Maybe then we'll truly be father and son.

756
01:10:01,399 --> 01:10:05,279
I'll never love you less.
I'll only love you more every day.

757
01:10:06,000 --> 01:10:09,920
What if you stopped loving me?
What would happen?

758
01:10:11,000 --> 01:10:12,239
I won't stop loving you.

759
01:10:15,760 --> 01:10:17,000
DELETE FILE

760
01:10:17,079 --> 01:10:17,920
DELETING

761
01:10:26,760 --> 01:10:28,279
Am I bad enough for you now?

762
01:10:28,800 --> 01:10:31,640
My only mistake was falling
for a woman like you!

763
01:11:46,439 --> 01:11:48,640
Hey! What's with all this noise?

764
01:11:49,319 --> 01:11:51,640
Go to sleep! I told you to go to sleep!

765
01:11:51,720 --> 01:11:52,560
Yes, sir.

766
01:12:32,920 --> 01:12:34,439
Bro.

767
01:12:35,119 --> 01:12:35,960
Look at that.

768
01:12:38,039 --> 01:12:39,720
Who says jailbirds are useless?

769
01:12:39,800 --> 01:12:42,680
At least those guys can earn money
for their families from here.

770
01:12:44,039 --> 01:12:44,880
I've heard

771
01:12:45,560 --> 01:12:46,760
that an order came in.

772
01:12:47,359 --> 01:12:49,319
They can earn money by selling organs.

773
01:12:49,920 --> 01:12:51,119
If your organ is a match,

774
01:12:51,199 --> 01:12:52,720
they'll pay through the nose.

775
01:12:52,800 --> 01:12:54,279
They don't care who you are.

776
01:13:01,960 --> 01:13:03,199
Gla!

777
01:13:08,600 --> 01:13:09,439
Gla.

778
01:13:11,039 --> 01:13:12,119
Come back.

779
01:13:13,399 --> 01:13:14,439
Gla.

780
01:13:52,279 --> 01:13:54,680
Gaogla has hanged himself in jail.

781
01:13:55,680 --> 01:13:59,359
To run away from his problems?
I never thought he'd be such a coward.

782
01:14:00,159 --> 01:14:02,760
It's like he knew
we've been arranging his divorce.

783
01:14:13,960 --> 01:14:15,000
What's going on?

784
01:14:19,239 --> 01:14:21,279
Did something happen to Gaogla?

785
01:14:24,560 --> 01:14:25,560
What happened?

786
01:14:27,520 --> 01:14:30,000
Dad, please just tell me.

787
01:14:30,079 --> 01:14:31,439
What happened, Dad?

788
01:14:32,199 --> 01:14:36,399
Dad, please tell me.
I'm begging you. I want to know.

789
01:14:36,479 --> 01:14:37,840
Dad, please tell me.

790
01:14:40,600 --> 01:14:42,760
Please, Dad? Please just tell me.

791
01:14:47,479 --> 01:14:48,600
He attempted suicide

792
01:14:49,199 --> 01:14:50,039
in jail.

793
01:14:53,520 --> 01:14:55,119
His condition is serious.

794
01:14:55,199 --> 01:14:56,479
We don't know if he'll live.

795
01:15:16,840 --> 01:15:18,600
How did it end up like this?

796
01:15:21,199 --> 01:15:22,720
I…

797
01:15:22,800 --> 01:15:23,960
-I have to see him.
-Khim.

798
01:15:24,039 --> 01:15:25,079
-Miss Khim.
-Khim.

799
01:15:25,159 --> 01:15:26,560
-You can't go anywhere.
-Don't.

800
01:15:26,640 --> 01:15:28,000
-No.
-Listen to me, honey.

801
01:15:28,840 --> 01:15:29,680
Khim.

802
01:15:30,720 --> 01:15:31,600
Khim.

803
01:15:33,119 --> 01:15:33,960
Listen, honey.

804
01:15:36,439 --> 01:15:37,640
You must forget him.

805
01:15:39,279 --> 01:15:40,840
You have to forget him!

806
01:15:43,479 --> 01:15:45,600
Even better, act like you never knew him.

807
01:15:48,000 --> 01:15:49,720
Start living your life again.

808
01:15:50,319 --> 01:15:51,159
Dad.

809
01:16:50,960 --> 01:16:53,960
We're going to move him
to scan his brain, sir.

810
01:17:05,920 --> 01:17:07,359
We have the results now.

811
01:17:07,439 --> 01:17:09,159
They are a match.

812
01:17:10,640 --> 01:17:14,279
Our doctor is prepping the operating room
for the kidney transplant.

813
01:17:29,479 --> 01:17:32,720
They found this contract in the jail.
Someone smuggled it to us.

814
01:17:38,600 --> 01:17:39,600
What does this mean?

815
01:17:40,239 --> 01:17:43,520
Your son has chosen
to give his organs to these traffickers

816
01:17:43,600 --> 01:17:45,520
and will receive something in return.

817
01:17:46,199 --> 01:17:47,319
But that's illegal.

818
01:17:47,399 --> 01:17:49,720
I don't understand
this crazy situation either.

819
01:17:49,800 --> 01:17:52,800
That's a person's whole life.
They can't just trade it!

820
01:17:52,880 --> 01:17:54,079
I hope he'll survive.

821
01:17:54,159 --> 01:17:57,119
But if he doesn't,
you should think about it.

822
01:17:57,800 --> 01:17:59,520
Would you let him die for nothing?

823
01:18:01,159 --> 01:18:04,560
We're going to move him
to scan his brain, sir.

824
01:18:05,199 --> 01:18:07,239
They were going to scan his brain.

825
01:18:12,720 --> 01:18:13,560
Gla!

826
01:18:20,680 --> 01:18:21,520
Where is he going?

827
01:18:37,880 --> 01:18:39,000
What are you doing here?

828
01:18:39,079 --> 01:18:41,640
He's my husband's illegitimate son.

829
01:18:43,560 --> 01:18:44,399
So it's you.

830
01:18:45,359 --> 01:18:46,319
You followed us.

831
01:18:47,159 --> 01:18:48,439
You can't take him anywhere.

832
01:18:49,159 --> 01:18:52,760
You hid him away for decades
and couldn't take good care of him!

833
01:18:52,840 --> 01:18:53,920
I'm taking him!

834
01:18:54,000 --> 01:18:56,880
But he's still alive.
He could still wake up.

835
01:18:57,479 --> 01:18:59,039
I'm not going to kill him!

836
01:18:59,560 --> 01:19:02,039
I just want him
to help save my son's life!

837
01:19:02,640 --> 01:19:03,760
Well, he's my son too.

838
01:19:04,840 --> 01:19:06,199
Do you have any morals?

839
01:19:06,279 --> 01:19:08,399
He wasn't born
to be someone's spare parts.

840
01:19:09,079 --> 01:19:12,159
No matter how bad life is,
he has the right to live.

841
01:19:12,760 --> 01:19:13,680
All of us

842
01:19:14,760 --> 01:19:15,960
have one life each.

843
01:19:17,640 --> 01:19:19,840
Your money can't dictate
someone else's life.

844
01:19:21,920 --> 01:19:24,119
He will never wake up

845
01:19:24,840 --> 01:19:26,399
because his wife

846
01:19:26,479 --> 01:19:29,199
has already prepared
his treatment refusal forms.

847
01:19:29,279 --> 01:19:31,199
If anything happens,

848
01:19:31,279 --> 01:19:33,560
he'll be left to wait to die.

849
01:19:33,640 --> 01:19:35,159
No one can save him.

850
01:19:40,600 --> 01:19:43,640
Those people are the ones
who are going to kill him.

851
01:19:49,279 --> 01:19:50,880
I will not lose this chance

852
01:19:51,840 --> 01:19:53,039
because without him,

853
01:19:53,600 --> 01:19:54,960
my son will not live.

854
01:19:55,640 --> 01:19:59,920
If someone has to die,
someone else should at least get to live.

855
01:20:00,000 --> 01:20:01,800
It's better than both of them dying.

856
01:21:22,439 --> 01:21:23,960
That's Nate, my son.

857
01:21:25,319 --> 01:21:27,640
He had a mountain climbing accident.

858
01:21:28,239 --> 01:21:30,159
He never regained consciousness.

859
01:21:32,840 --> 01:21:35,720
We used equipment to support him

860
01:21:35,800 --> 01:21:38,920
and brought him here
to buy time and wait for a miracle.

861
01:21:39,439 --> 01:21:42,199
To me, your son is that miracle

862
01:21:42,840 --> 01:21:45,960
because three days ago,
Nate had kidney failure.

863
01:21:54,680 --> 01:21:56,039
Tissue forceps, please.

864
01:22:00,720 --> 01:22:02,199
Your son is in great danger.

865
01:22:02,279 --> 01:22:03,840
You really think he'll survive?

866
01:22:04,520 --> 01:22:06,600
How many days will Gla buy him, huh?

867
01:22:06,680 --> 01:22:08,600
I'll buy as many days as I can

868
01:22:08,680 --> 01:22:11,079
because Nate grew up
with this deadly condition

869
01:22:11,159 --> 01:22:12,560
and he's survived this long.

870
01:22:12,640 --> 01:22:16,279
He needs a liver today.
Maybe tomorrow it'll be a lung or a heart.

871
01:22:18,800 --> 01:22:20,199
Let me tell you something.

872
01:22:21,600 --> 01:22:22,439
Gla

873
01:22:23,479 --> 01:22:25,319
is a miracle to me too.

874
01:22:28,279 --> 01:22:29,760
He tried to kill himself,

875
01:22:31,520 --> 01:22:34,359
meaning he didn't want
to donate just his kidney.

876
01:22:34,960 --> 01:22:39,000
He wanted to save his sister's life
by giving his own in exchange.

877
01:22:41,880 --> 01:22:43,079
That's the kind of heart

878
01:22:44,199 --> 01:22:45,760
that deserves to be loved,

879
01:22:46,960 --> 01:22:48,039
not destroyed.

880
01:22:50,439 --> 01:22:51,920
That miracle of yours

881
01:22:53,520 --> 01:22:55,359
is his heart!

882
01:22:56,720 --> 01:22:58,680
He has had to live in the shadows

883
01:22:58,760 --> 01:23:02,560
to hide from a father
who doesn't treat him like a human.

884
01:23:03,840 --> 01:23:06,560
He got arrested after being bullied
for not being my own son.

885
01:23:07,079 --> 01:23:09,479
We've ruined their childhood

886
01:23:09,560 --> 01:23:12,039
by making them face grown-up problems.

887
01:23:12,600 --> 01:23:14,359
We've acted like we own them.

888
01:23:17,199 --> 01:23:18,720
From the cradle to the grave,

889
01:23:18,800 --> 01:23:21,199
we've never let them live their own lives,

890
01:23:21,279 --> 01:23:23,199
and now we're even taking their lives.

891
01:23:24,199 --> 01:23:25,800
How could you do this to him?

892
01:23:33,920 --> 01:23:37,479
I'm begging you.
Please give Gla's life back to me.

893
01:23:57,079 --> 01:23:58,600
-Blood pressure drop.
-How much?

894
01:23:59,119 --> 01:24:00,479
Fifty over seventy, Doctor.

895
01:24:01,319 --> 01:24:03,199
Prep one unit of blood, stat.

896
01:24:25,960 --> 01:24:26,800
Attention.

897
01:24:26,880 --> 01:24:29,039
The following flight has been suspended…

898
01:24:29,119 --> 01:24:30,079
Start CPR.

899
01:24:30,600 --> 01:24:32,119
-Now!
-Yes, Doctor.

900
01:24:36,039 --> 01:24:38,279
-Any increase?
-Heart rate dropping.

901
01:25:21,560 --> 01:25:22,680
Khim, what's wrong?

902
01:25:30,960 --> 01:25:31,840
Gla!

903
01:25:32,640 --> 01:25:33,479
Don't die!

904
01:26:00,239 --> 01:26:01,319
I gotta go.

905
01:26:04,159 --> 01:26:05,000
Gla!

906
01:26:08,760 --> 01:26:09,760
Gla!

907
01:26:10,359 --> 01:26:11,279
Stay strong!

908
01:26:12,000 --> 01:26:13,319
Don't die, Gla!

909
01:26:27,880 --> 01:26:29,319
I won't stop loving you.

910
01:26:30,640 --> 01:26:31,880
If I stopped loving you,

911
01:26:32,920 --> 01:26:34,199
it'd be because I'd died.

912
01:26:39,239 --> 01:26:40,680
Gla!

913
01:27:22,920 --> 01:27:24,039
Khim, what's wrong?

914
01:27:43,359 --> 01:27:45,239
Because love is fragile…

915
01:27:48,439 --> 01:27:51,119
only love can heal love.

916
01:27:56,319 --> 01:27:58,239
When we have to say goodbye…

917
01:28:23,279 --> 01:28:24,439
You can only hope that…

918
01:28:25,399 --> 01:28:27,159
we'll still dare to love again.

919
01:28:40,199 --> 01:28:41,159
Hey, Tan.

920
01:28:41,800 --> 01:28:44,560
Dry your hair first, oppa,
then dry yourself all over.

921
01:28:46,239 --> 01:28:48,560
He's in the past now.

922
01:28:48,640 --> 01:28:50,520
Even if he had lived,

923
01:28:50,600 --> 01:28:52,359
you're way out of his league.

924
01:28:52,439 --> 01:28:53,640
Anyway, now,

925
01:28:54,279 --> 01:28:56,720
you're in a serious relationship.

926
01:28:57,680 --> 01:28:59,119
Marry me.

927
01:29:02,079 --> 01:29:04,079
Do you know someone in heaven, miss?

928
01:29:04,159 --> 01:29:05,960
You can send them a letter.

929
01:29:06,479 --> 01:29:08,560
I don't know if he's still up there.

930
01:29:08,640 --> 01:29:10,079
It's been seven years.

931
01:29:10,600 --> 01:29:13,119
Miss Khim hasn't called yet.
She must be on the island.

932
01:29:13,199 --> 01:29:15,079
Why did you let her go alone?

933
01:29:18,520 --> 01:29:20,119
I'll follow you there.

934
